  "body": "# Problem\nIOS pings `apple.com` via `NetInfo` for connectivity checks.\n\n## Description\nIt looks like IOS is pinging `apple.com` for checking if the device is connected \n\nhttps://github.com/facebook/react-native/blob/eebc8e230a9f72c3dde34a5cfd59bbffba55e53d/Libraries/Network/RCTNetInfo.m#L127\n\nI have only verified this by code inspection and not actually checking the connections made to the app, so it might not be the case.\n\nIdeally for privacy concern we should either not use `NetInfo` and rely on `peers` count or at least use something safer for this.\n\nRelated to: https://github.com/status-im/react-native-desktop/issues/378\n\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/69631?s=400&v=4\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div>![](https://assets-cdn.github.com/favicon.ico)GitHub</div><div><strong>[facebook/react-native](https://github.com/facebook/react-native)</strong></div><div>A framework for building native apps with React. Contribute to facebook/react-native development by creating an account on GitHub.</div></blockquote>",
